	* config file

	* -p PASSWORD [ -s SERVER ]... [ -H HOST ] [ -m MASK ]...
  	  --password=  --server=  --bind-host=  --from-mask=
	  specifies the only connection class that can be used.  There must
	  be one -s parameter of course.  Automatically turns off reading
	  connection classes from the config file

	* -f CONFIGFILE, --config-file=CONFIGFILE
	  specifies an alternate config file (otherwise ~/.dircproxyrc)

	* -P PORT, --listen-port=PORT
	  config file override

	* --rejoin-after-kick=VALUE --server-retry=VALUE
	    --server-dns-retry=VALUE --server-max-attempts=VALUE
	    --server-max-init-attempts=VALUE --detach-away-message=VALUE
	  config file overrides

	* --server-retry=VALUES
	  config
	  time between server retries


